06:41.276 --> 06:42.485
-[Sarah] Morning.

06:48.575 --> 06:50.702
-I thought you wanted me to do that.

06:51.369 --> 06:53.496
-[Sarah] No, I was up early.

06:54.205 --> 06:55.916
You can do it tomorrow.

07:02.714 --> 07:04.341
Do you have a little one?

07:05.133 --> 07:06.301
-What?

07:08.553 --> 07:09.804
Oh.

07:15.143 --> 07:18.730
-I would have a--
a baby right now if Daddy would let me.

07:18.813 --> 07:20.398
[laughs]

07:30.367 --> 07:33.328
The last guy who worked here had five kids.

07:38.208 --> 07:39.250
Did you hear me?

07:39.334 --> 07:40.627
-YUP-

07:51.596 --> 07:56.601
<i>I"Murder, He Says"
by Betty Hutton plays on TVS'</i>

08:10.490 --> 08:11.866
[loud gunshot]

08:20.417 --> 08:21.418
[gunshot]

08:30.677 --> 08:33.388
-[Jeremiah] We're gonna have
to make some hard decisions.

08:34.431 --> 08:36.433
-[Sarah] [crying softly]

08:40.437 --> 08:42.897
-[Jeremiah] Now, it's gonna
be hard to look at, all right?

08:42.981 --> 08:44.274
-[Sarah] [crying softly]

08:49.070 --> 08:51.364
-[Jeremiah] [whispering] Hello, sweetie.

08:51.448 --> 08:54.034
Come on and say goodbye to her, sweetheart.

08:54.868 --> 08:57.203
-[Sarah] [whispering] Come on.
[horse grunts]

08:57.287 --> 08:59.372
-[Sarah] [whispering] [inaudible] upset.

08:59.456 --> 09:00.915
Hey.

09:04.836 --> 09:06.212
I'm sorry.

09:09.424 --> 09:11.092
It's okay.

09:12.927 --> 09:14.345
Yeah.

09:15.889 --> 09:18.058
[horse grunting]

09:19.434 --> 09:21.561
-[Jeremiah] [whispering] Sweet baby, yes.

09:23.730 --> 09:25.482
She likes that.

09:28.276 --> 09:29.944
[metallic clicking]

09:35.283 --> 09:37.744
-[Sarah VO] My lover
did not fall down from the sky

09:37.827 --> 09:39.662
or grow up from the earth.

09:41.206 --> 09:47.170
My lover...does not have hands
like hands I've known.

09:48.379 --> 09:50.882
<i>♪ up lifting ambient strings ♪</i>

09:50.965 --> 09:53.134
Urn...

09:54.928 --> 09:59.432
My lover can touch me everywhere at once.

09:59.516 --> 10:02.268
<i>III'</i>

10:22.205 --> 10:23.289
[door slams]

10:27.335 --> 10:30.463
-[Jeremiah] How much work have
you done in your life, son, like this?

10:30.547 --> 10:32.382
Pick the fork up to your mouth.

10:33.133 --> 10:35.552
-[Akin] I usually do cellar work.

10:36.344 --> 10:39.430
Carpentry and house paint.

10:39.514 --> 10:43.643
-My ass you do house painting,
scraggled-up shoulders like that.

10:43.726 --> 10:45.311
Somebody tell you to say that, son?

10:45.395 --> 10:46.813
-[Akin] No, sir.

10:47.522 --> 10:48.481
-[Sarah] He used to work in a school.

10:48.565 --> 10:50.150
